I admire this restaurant! They offer high quality food, their menu is large, The chief cook in that place is a real pro, I enjoy a lot tasting all their food. The dishes are always good, the service towards the guests  is very good too. I often eat in this restaurant and I not even once was discontended. I recommend this place.

This restaurant is OK, overall. Their red bean soup with beef and pigtail is AMAZING. I could eat it all day. On the other hand, I bought a large oxtail with rice and peas for $18 and received only FOUR mediocre pieces of oxtail. Are they serious?  I wish they would take customer reviews and feedback seriously.

Food was delivered quickly which I appreciate. Unfortunately, the jerk pork was a bit dry and it was covered in a sauce that was way too salty. I usually like salt but this was overbearing. The plantains were fine. I did however, really enjoy the rice & peas. This place was mediocre. I would give 2.5 stars but I’ll round it to 3. Not sure if I would return. Only certain places have mastered jerk pork and this is not one of them. Hopefully they were just having an off day. I can’t speak on their other menu items. I only tried this place because my normal go to restaurant is not available right now.

One of my favorites. The menu can vary depending on availability of ingredients.  Their business is mostly take-out, but they have some tables and we eat in and take out.  My Jamaican friends say the food reminds them of back home. Run by nice people well like by the community.  Some dishes can be spicy, some are mild, as is typical of Jamaican cuisine, but something for everybody.
